  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5 during continuous-flow left ventricular assist device support at 3–6 L/min cardiac output and 60–120 mmHg differential pressure. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; 7 achieved required levels and 6 remain below required levels but were accepted under a risk-informed rationale by the credibility assessment team. Decision: Accepted.",
